mimosaPtmp.description: The MIB module for Mimosa PTMP products

mimosaPtmpSsidTable.name: mimosaPtmpSsidTable
mimosaPtmpSsidTable.description: A list of A5 SSID entries

mimosaPtmpSsidEntry.name: mimosaPtmpSsidEntry
mimosaPtmpSsidEntry.description: Entry that describes each SSID and all its related configuration

mimosaPtmpSsidIndex.name: mimosaPtmpSsidIndex
mimosaPtmpSsidIndex.description: Describes the index used to access a particular entry in the SSID table.

mimosaPtmpSsidName.name: mimosaPtmpSsidName
mimosaPtmpSsidName.description: Describes the name of the SSID

mimosaPtmpSsidType.name: mimosaPtmpSsidType
mimosaPtmpSsidType.description: Describes the type of clients that will connect to this SSID. CPE represents fixed, or Hotspot represents mobile devices

mimosaPtmpSsidEnabled.name: mimosaPtmpSsidEnabled
mimosaPtmpSsidEnabled.description: Describes if the SSID is enabled (True) or disabled (False)

mimosaPtmpSsidBroadcastEnabled.name: mimosaPtmpSsidBroadcastEnabled
mimosaPtmpSsidBroadcastEnabled.description: Describes if the Broadcast feature for this SSID is enabled or disabled

mimosaPtmpSsidIsolationEnabled.name: mimosaPtmpSsidIsolationEnabled
mimosaPtmpSsidIsolationEnabled.description: Describes if the client isolation is enabled or disabled

mimosaPtmpWirelessMode.name: mimosaPtmpWirelessMode
mimosaPtmpWirelessMode.description: Describes the wireless protocol configured on the Mimosa Device

mimosaPtmpWirelessGender.name: mimosaPtmpWirelessGender
mimosaPtmpWirelessGender.description: Describes the wireless protocol gender that defines the transmit and receive timing

mimosaPtmpWirelessTrafficSplit.name: mimosaPtmpWirelessTrafficSplit
mimosaPtmpWirelessTrafficSplit.description: Describes how the bandwidth is split between the AP and Station

mimosaPtmpWirelessWindowLength.name: mimosaPtmpWirelessWindowLength
mimosaPtmpWirelessWindowLength.description: Describes the length of the transmit time slot in milliseconds

mimosaPtmpAutoChannelEnabled.name: mimosaPtmpAutoChannelEnabled
mimosaPtmpAutoChannelEnabled.description: Describes if the Auto Channel feature is Enabled or Disabled. This function selects the channel that results in the best RF performance.

mimosaPtmpAntennaGain.name: mimosaPtmpAntennaGain
mimosaPtmpAntennaGain.description: Describes the antenna gain for connectorized version of the device. Measured in dBi.

mimosaPtmpChannelPowerTable.name: mimosaPtmpChannelPowerTable
mimosaPtmpChannelPowerTable.description: A list of Channel and Power related information per radio.

mimosaPtmpChannelPowerEntry.name: mimosaPtmpChannelPowerEntry
mimosaPtmpChannelPowerEntry.description: An entry containing channel and power information

mimosaPtmpChPwrRadioIndex.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrRadioIndex
mimosaPtmpChPwrRadioIndex.description: Describes the index of the radio.

mimosaPtmpChPwrRadioName.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrRadioName
mimosaPtmpChPwrRadioName.description: Describes the name of the radio.

mimosaPtmpChPwrCntrFreqCfg.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrCntrFreqCfg
mimosaPtmpChPwrCntrFreqCfg.description: Describes the configured center frequency of the channel used on the access point. The center frequency represents the absolute center of the selected channel width without any offset. Measured in MHz

mimosaPtmpChPwrPrimChannelCfg.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrPrimChannelCfg
mimosaPtmpChPwrPrimChannelCfg.description: Describes the primary channel number that corresponds with the operating frequency.

mimosaPtmpChPwrChWidthCfg.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrChWidthCfg
mimosaPtmpChPwrChWidthCfg.description: Describes the channel width for access point operation: 20 MHz, 40 MHz or 80 MHz

mimosaPtmpChPwrTxPowerCfg.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrTxPowerCfg
mimosaPtmpChPwrTxPowerCfg.description: Describes the desired transmit power level. The allowed options are determined by a combination of country and chosen frequency. Measured in dBm

mimosaPtmpChPwrCntrFreqCur.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrCntrFreqCur
mimosaPtmpChPwrCntrFreqCur.description: Describes the current center frequency of the channel used on the access point. The center frequency represents the absolute center of the selected channel width without any offset. Measured in MHz

mimosaPtmpChPwrPrimChannelCur.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrPrimChannelCur
mimosaPtmpChPwrPrimChannelCur.description: Describes the current primary channel number that corresponds with the operating frequency.

mimosaPtmpChPwrChWidthCur.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrChWidthCur
mimosaPtmpChPwrChWidthCur.description: Describes the current channel width for access point operation: 20 MHz, 40 MHz or 80 MHz

mimosaPtmpChPwrTxPowerCur.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrTxPowerCur
mimosaPtmpChPwrTxPowerCur.description: Describes the current transmit power level. The allowed options are determined by a combination of country and chosen frequency. Measured in dBm

mimosaPtmpChPwrAgcMode.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrAgcMode
mimosaPtmpChPwrAgcMode.description: Describes the setting for Automatic Gain Control (AGC) feature, which is used to set the signal level below which the radio ignores incoming RF interference. The choices are Off or Manual

mimosaPtmpChPwrMinRxPower.name: mimosaPtmpChPwrMinRxPower
mimosaPtmpChPwrMinRxPower.description: Describes the Rx power level (in manual AGC Mode) below your expected signal, but above other interference, measured in dBm

mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionTable.name: mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionTable
mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionTable.description: A list of Exclusions and Restrictions

mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionEntry.name: mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionEntry
mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionEntry.description: Entry that describes each SSID and all its related configuration

mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionIndex.name: mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionIndex
mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionIndex.description: Describes the index used to access a particular entry in the Exclusion list table.

mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionStart.name: mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionStart
mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionStart.description: Describes the lower limit for the exclusion range, not including this frequency

mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionEnd.name: mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionEnd
mimosaPtmpChannelExclusionEnd.description: Describes the upper limit for the exclusion range, not including this frequency.

mimosaPtmpApStatsRxBytes.name: mimosaPtmpApStatsRxBytes
mimosaPtmpApStatsRxBytes.description: Describes the number of bytes received by the AP in single-User mode

mimosaPtmpApStatsTxBytes.name: mimosaPtmpApStatsTxBytes
mimosaPtmpApStatsTxBytes.description: Describes the number of bytes transmitted by the AP in single-user mode

mimosaPtmpApStatsRxPkts.name: mimosaPtmpApStatsRxPkts
mimosaPtmpApStatsRxPkts.description: Describes the number of packets received by the AP in single-user mode

mimosaPtmpApStatsTxPkts.name: mimosaPtmpApStatsTxPkts
mimosaPtmpApStatsTxPkts.description: Describes the number of packets transmitted by the AP in single-user mode

mimosaPtmpApStatsTxPer.name: mimosaPtmpApStatsTxPer
mimosaPtmpApStatsTxPer.description: Describes the packet error rate on the transmit path of the AP, in single-user mode

mimosaPtmpApStatsLastUpdated.name: mimosaPtmpApStatsLastUpdated
mimosaPtmpApStatsLastUpdated.description: Describes the last updated time for these statistics

mimosaPtmpClientInfoTable.name: mimosaPtmpClientInfoTable

mimosaPtmpClientInfoEntry.description: Entry that describes each client and related configuration and statistics.

mimosaPtmpClientInfoIndex.name: mimosaPtmpClientInfoIndex
mimosaPtmpClientInfoIndex.description: Describes the index used to access a particular entry in the Client Traffic Shaping Information table.

mimosaPtmpClientInfoMacAddress.name: mimosaPtmpClientInfoMacAddress
mimosaPtmpClientInfoMacAddress.description: Describes the MAC address of the client associated to this access- point.

mimosaPtmpClientName.name: mimosaPtmpClientName
mimosaPtmpClientName.description: Describes the name associated with this client.

mimosaPtmpClientFWVersion.name: mimosaPtmpClientFWVersion
mimosaPtmpClientFWVersion.description: Describes the firmware version of this client. This is supported only if the client is a Mimosa device.

mimosaPtmpClientIPAddress.name: mimosaPtmpClientIPAddress
mimosaPtmpClientIPAddress.description: Describes the IP Address associated with this client.

mimosaPtmpClientAssociatedTime.name: mimosaPtmpClientAssociatedTime
mimosaPtmpClientAssociatedTime.description: Describes how long the client is associated with this access-point.

mimosaPtmpClientPlanName.name: mimosaPtmpClientPlanName
mimosaPtmpClientPlanName.description: Describes the Traffic Shaping plan associated with this client.

mimosaPtmpClientUlCommitted.description: Describes the Uplink Committed Rate configured for the client.

mimosaPtmpClientUlPeak.name: mimosaPtmpClientUlPeak
mimosaPtmpClientUlPeak.description: Describes the Uplink Peak Rate configured for the client.

mimosaPtmpClientDlCommitted.name: mimosaPtmpClientDlCommitted
mimosaPtmpClientDlCommitted.description: Describes the Downlink Committed Rate configured for the client.

mimosaPtmpClientDlPeak.description: Describes the Downlink Peak Rate configured for the client.

mimosaPtmpClientInfoLastUpdated.description: Describes the last updated time of this information for the Client.

mimosaPtmpClientStatsMacAddress.description: Describes the MAC address of the client associated to this access- point.
